description: Returns a list of robots. You can optionally provide filters to retrieve specific robots.

parameters.name: filters
parameters.description: Optional filters to limit results. The filter names status and fleetName are supported. When filtering, you must use the complete value of the filtered item. You can use up to three filters, but they must be for the same named item. For example, if you are looking for items with the status Registered or the status Available. (dict) --- Information about a filter. name (string) --- The name of the filter. values (list) --- A list of values. (string) ---

nested_items.name: robots
nested_items.description: A list of robots that meet the criteria of the request.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the robot.

nested_items.name: fleetArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the fleet.

nested_items.name: greenGrassGroupId
nested_items.description: The Greengrass group associated with the robot.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The time, in milliseconds since the epoch, when the robot was created.

nested_items.name: lastDeploymentJob
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the last deployment job.

nested_items.name: lastDeploymentTime
nested_items.description: The time of the last deployment.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: If the previous paginated request did not return all of the remaining results, the response object's nextToken parameter value is set to a token. To retrieve the next set of results, call ListRobots again and assign that token to the request object's nextToken parameter. If there are no remaining results, the previous response object's NextToken parameter is set to null.
